Company Overview of Parkview Capital Credit, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Parkview Capital Credit, Inc. is a private equity firm specializing in mezzanine debt, equity capital, subordinated debt, buyout, recapitalizations, refinancing’s and strategic growth to lower middle market companies. The firm typically invests in companies based in North America. It usually invests between $3 million and $10 million per transaction in companies with EBITDA of less than $25 million and annual revenue between $20 million and $200 million. The firm usually makes takes an observation/Board of Director Seat. It makes investment for a period of 4 to 6 years and usually takes a stake of between 5% and 15%. The firm typically exits the investment by liquidation of company, sale of ...
Parkview Capital Credit, Inc. is a private equity firm specializing in mezzanine debt, equity capital, subordinated debt, buyout, recapitalizations, refinancing’s and strategic growth to lower middle market companies. The firm typically invests in companies based in North America. It usually invests between $3 million and $10 million per transaction in companies with EBITDA of less than $25 million and annual revenue between $20 million and $200 million. The firm usually makes takes an observation/Board of Director Seat. It makes investment for a period of 4 to 6 years and usually takes a stake of between 5% and 15%. The firm typically exits the investment by liquidation of company, sale of collateral, and strategic acquisition. Parkview Capital Credit, Inc. is based in Houston, Texas.
