Parkview Capital Credit, Inc. Key Developments

Parkview Capital Credit Announces 2016 Initial Cash Distribution
Dec 22 16
Parkview Capital Credit, Inc. announced that its Board of Directors has approved its initial cash distribution of $1,077,060 or $0.28 per share to the stockholders of the Company of record as of December 21, 2016. The distribution was made on December 22, 2016 and is equivalent to 98% of Parkview Capital’s estimated taxable income for the fiscal year ending December 31, 2016.


Parkview Capital Credit, Inc. Nominates Bert Beal as Class One Director
May 19 16
On April 25, 2016, the board of directors of Parkview Capital Credit, Inc. nominated Bert Beal as a Class One director of the company to serve a three-year term expiring at the 2019 annual meeting of stockholders. Mr. Beal was nominated to fill the vacancy created by David M. Abner's resignation from the Board effective April 1, 2016.


Parkview Capital Credit, Inc. Announces the Resignation of David M. Abner from the Board of Directors
Apr 6 16
On March 31, 2016, Parkview Capital Credit, Inc. received the resignation of David M. Abner from the Board of Directors of the company, effective April 1, 2016. Upon his resignation, Mr. Abner intends to provide legal services to Parkview Advisors, LLC, the company's affiliate and investment adviser.


